@section Compiling Java Programs

To compile the source file in the current buffer, select JDEE->Compile,
type @kbd{C-c-C-v-C-c}, or execute @kbd{M-x jdee-compile}. The compiler
uses the version of javac included in the currently selected JDK or on
your system command path by default. However, you can configure the
JDEE to use another compiler for the current project or all projects
(see Specifying a Compiler). The JDEE also allows you to configure the
JDEE to invoke the compiler with various compilation options.

