@section Running Java Applications

The JDEE allows you to run a Java application as an Emacs
subprocess. You can run multiple applications concurrently, but only
one instance of each application at a time. The JDEE displays each
application's standard and error output in an Emacs command interface
(comint) buffer. You can interact with applications that accept
command line input via the comint buffer. When interacting with an
application, you can use any of comint-mode's extensive set of
command-line history commands to speed interaction.

To run an application, enter @kbd{M-x jdee-run} or select Java->Run App
from the Emacs menubar or type @kbd{C-c C-v C-r}.

