can recall previously entered options by pressing the up or down
arrows on your keyboard.

@node Setting Command-Line Application Arguments, Navigating Exception Traces, Setting VM Command-Line Arguments, Running Java Applications
@subsection Setting Command-Line Application Arguments

Specifying a prefix argument before the jdee-run, e.g., C-u C-c C-v C-r
causes the command to prompt you to enter arguments to be passed to
the application's main method. The command appends the options that
you enter to the arguments specified via the customization variable
jdee-run-option-application-args. The JDEE saves the arguments that you
